  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Complaint to the COPE Committee against the Governor of the Central Bank",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The members of the 'COPE' Committee requested to pay attention to Sri Lanka turning to the International Monetary Fund with serious conditions after Sri Lanka's Central Bank Governor Mr. Nandalal Weerasinghe decided to default on the payment of international sovereign bonds and to receive serious decisions from the case filed in America regarding the debt default. A letter has been sent to Mr. Charita Herath.",
        "It is mentioned in the letter addressed by the \"Professionals' National Front\" that due to debt default, Sri Lankan government revenues will have to be frozen and banned before they reach the country.",
        "In the letter written by Mr. Engineer Kapila Renuka Perera, Chairman of the National Front of Professionals, it has been mentioned that the Governor of the Central Bank has ignored the Minister of Finance, the Cabinet and the President while the Parliament has full control over the public finances of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka."
      ],
